com.github.tommyettinger.ds

Class FloatList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.tommyettinger.ds.FloatList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Arrangeable, java.io.Serializable

    public class FloatList
extends java.lang.Object
implements Arrangeable, java.io.Serializable
    A resizable, ordered or unordered float list. Primitive-backed, so it avoids the boxing that occurs with an ArrayList of Float. If unordered, this class avoids a memory copy when removing elements (the last element is moved to the removed element's position). This tries to imitate most of the List interface, though it can't implement it without boxing its items.

      • removeAll

        public boolean removeAll(FloatList array)
        Removes from this array all of elements contained in the specified array. Note that if a value is present more than once in this FloatList, only one of those occurrences will be removed for each occurrence of that value in array. If array has the same contents as this FloatList or has additional items, then removing all of array will clear this.
        Returns:
        true if this array was modified.
